Class MarkPassingsData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tractrac.clientmodule.details.Attachments
      • com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.TimeObject
        • com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.MarkPassingsData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimeObject>

    public class MarkPassingsData
extends TimeObject
    Represents mark passings for a RaceCompetitor.

    The static method subscribe(com.tractrac.clientmodule.Race, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.ICallbackData<com.tractrac.clientmodule.RaceCompetitor, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.MarkPassingsData>) can be used to receive positions.

    Custom data may be attached to each class instance.

    Version:
    2.0

      • subscribe

        public static com.maptrack.client.io.TypeController subscribe(Race race,
                                              ICallbackData<RaceCompetitor,MarkPassingsData> callback)
        Sets up a subscription for mark passings for a given Race.

        The method returns immediately and the data are subsequently sent to a given callback, as they are received.

        The returned type controller should be added to a DataController.

        Parameters:
        race - the race from which to request the data
        callback - the callback to receive the data
        Returns:
        the type controller
